@startuml
!include ../../styles/plantuml-theme.puml

left to right direction
title FIG-12-04. Horizon Bank Payment Threat-Model DFD

skinparam rectangle {
  BorderColor #333333
  BackgroundColor #F7F9FB
}
skinparam component {
  BorderColor #333333
  BackgroundColor #FFFFFF
}
skinparam database {
  BorderColor #333333
  BackgroundColor #F2F5F7
}
skinparam queue {
  BorderColor #333333
  BackgroundColor #F2F5F7
}

actor "Retail\nCustomer" as Customer
actor "Operations\nAnalyst" as Ops
actor "Compliance\nOfficer" as Compliance

rectangle "Customer Access Context\nboundary basis:\ncustomer device and\nsession presentation" as CustomerContext {
  component "Horizon Digital\nChannels" as Channels
}

rectangle "Payment Platform Responsibility\nboundary basis:\npayment orchestration policy" as PaymentContext {
  component "Payments\nPlatform" as Payments
  database "Payment\nRecord Store" as PaymentStore
  database "Audit Log" as AuditLog
}

rectangle "Financial-Crime Responsibility\nboundary basis:\npolicy authority" as FinancialCrimeContext {
  component "Financial Crime\nPlatform" as FinancialCrime
}

rectangle "Retained Core Responsibility\nboundary basis:\ncore account posting" as CoreContext {
  database "Core Deposit\nSystem" as Core
}

rectangle "Event Distribution Context\nboundary basis:\nevent governance and\nconsumer access" as EventContext {
  queue "Event Platform" as EventPlatform
}

Customer --> Channels : payment instruction\nand session reference\n[T12-01]
Channels --> Payments : payment instruction,\nvalidated subject context\nand entitlement context\n[T12-02, T12-07]

Payments --> FinancialCrime : screening request
FinancialCrime --> Payments : screening result\n[T12-05]
Compliance --> FinancialCrime : screening case action\n[T12-05]

Ops --> Payments : controlled repair action\n[T12-04, T12-08]

Payments --> Core : posting request\n[T12-03]
Core --> Payments : posting result

Payments --> PaymentStore : store payment record
Payments --> AuditLog : write audit event\n[T12-04]
Payments --> EventPlatform : payment-status event\n[T12-06]

legend bottom
Threat IDs label review points, not proof of vulnerability.
Authentication and session validation are represented in the authentication model, not as a full Identity Service flow here.
DFD elements are external entities, processes, stores and data flows, not BPMN process steps.
endlegend
@enduml
